    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>All sediment particles, regardless of mineral origin, that fall within a specified size range between those of sand and clay. An unconsolidated aggregation of particles is also called silt; a consolidated aggregate, silt-stone.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
